The paper proposes an extension to a process calculus for modeling ecological systems, which involves specifying orderings between different activities within the system. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
